          </Label>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Section title="About">
      <p class="text-muted-foreground margin-0">
        As a seasoned Full-Stack Software Engineer with expertise in developing
        secure cloud and client based applications, I have honed my skills on a
        variety of projects, both small and complex. Driven by a passion for
        innovation, I continually strive to stay ahead of the curve by keeping
        up with the latest programming languages and technologies. Whether it's
        discovering new techniques to improve code efficiency or implementing
        cutting-edge features, I am dedicated to taking my projects and dream
        ideas to the next level. When not immersed in programming, I enjoy
        playing video games and following my favorite content creators on Twitch
        and YouTube, keeping up with the latest trends and developments in the
        industry.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Experience">
      <Card
        heading="Software Engineer III"
        subheading="Biomeme"
        date="May 2021 - Current"
        altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
        imageClass="h-12 w-auto md:-left-16"
      >
        <ul class="experience-list text-muted-foreground">
          <li>
            Led development of the backend architecture, API, and database for
            an intuitive online interface enabling employers to schedule
            medically diagnostic tests for their employees, increasing the
            overall efficiency for labs and employers.
          </li>
          <li>
            Contributed to several React webapps and React Native (Android)
            applications that interacted with a backend API and AWS.
          </li>
          <li>
            Created comprehensive Figma diagrams and mockups, shaping the
            implementation of new features and User Experience.
          </li>
          <li>
            Managed a variety of AWS services, including Lambda, ECS, API
            Gateway, RDS, IAM, Cognito, CloudWatch, CloudFormation, and S3, to
            build secure, scalable, and highly available cloud-based solutions
            for several of our projects.
          </li>
          <li>
            Automated build and deployment processes using CircleCI, reducing
            time to deployment and enhancing overall efficiency.
          </li>
          <li>
            Prioritized feature requests and addressed issues by leveraging data
            from tools like Sentry, CloudWatch, and Snyk.
          </li>
          <li>
            Utilized Jira to manage project tasks, stories, and sprints,
            ensuring team alignment and effective progress tracking.
          </li>
          <li>
            Provided mentorship, guidance, and knowledge to junior team members,
            contributing to their professional development.
          </li>
          <li>
            Earned a promotion to Seniority Level III by consistently surpassing
            role expectations, as recognized by management.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <Card
        heading="Software Engineer"
        subheading="Gnostech"
        date="Sept 2016 - May 2021"
        altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
        imageClass="h-12 w-auto md:-left-16"
      >
        <ul class="experience-list text-muted-foreground">
          <li>
            Led the design, development, and deployment of a microservice
            oriented architecture built upon DevOps principles utilizing AWS,
            Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform (Infrastructure as code), Gitlab
            CI/CD, and Spring Boot Cloud.
          </li>
          <li>
            Created a developer toolkit that significantly increased
            productivity, resulting in faster development time.
          </li>
          <li>
            Major Contributor and developer to the cloud-based patch management
            solution deployed and used by the US Navy.
          </li>
          <li>
            Spearheaded the design and development of a help desk management
            system with video streaming capabilities.
          </li>
          <li>
            Full-stack development on several applications leveraging Java 11,
            Spring Boot, MySQL, C#, WPF, Angular, Typescript, JSON.
          </li>
          <li>
            Identified and delivered a critical enhancement to the application,
            greatly improving security and stability.
          </li>
          <li>
            Interviewed and evaluated candidates for the software development
            team and mentored other members of the team.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Education">
      <Card
        heading="Masters of Science in Computer Science"
        subheading="Rowan University"
        date="Sept 2016 - May 2019"
        altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
        imageClass="h-12 w-auto md:-left-16"
      >
        <ul class="experience-list text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Graduated with Magna Cum Laude Honors</li>
          <li>
            Completed coursework in advanced algorithms, operating systems,
            cybersecurity, and cryptography.
          </li>
          <li>
            Collaborated with faculty and peers on research projects and
            academic initiatives.
          </li>
          <li>
            Received commendation for leadership and teamwork skills during
            group projects.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
      <Card
        heading="Bachelors of Science in Biological Science"
        subheading="Rowan University"
        date="Sept 2011 - May 2016"
        imagePath="/src/assets/about-astro.png"
        altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
        imageClass="h-12 w-auto md:-left-16"
      >
        <ul class="experience-list text-muted-foreground">
          <li>Minored in computer science and chemistry</li>
          <li>Ecological Individual Based Model Developer</li>
          <ul class="sub-list text-muted-foreground">
            <li>
              Faculty supported, independent research on the endangered seagrass <i
                >Halophila johnsonii</i
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              Worked with large NOAA data sets as training data for the model
              development
            </li>
            <li>
              Pesented final research and model at the 2016 STEM symposium
            </li>
          </ul>
          <li>Artificial Intelligence Developer</li>
          <ul class="sub-list text-muted-foreground">
            <li>
              Developed and implemented a minimax inspired algorithm into a
              unique card based game
            </li>
            <li>Presented the final product at the 2016 STEM symposium</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Projects">
      <div class="project-container">
        <ProjectCard
          href="https://www.google.com"
          heading="Animal Crossing Critters"
          subheading="Help keep track and fill out your Animal Crossing New Horizons Critterpedia by using this tracker to see which critters you have captured and see when each critter is available."
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/animal-crossing.svg"
          altText="Example"
          class="project-image"
		  style="background-color: #54db00";
        />
        <ProjectCard
          as="div"
          heading="SuperNova: Escape!"
          subheading="Tap to escape the trailing super nova in this endless arcade classic! Carefully avoid the asteroids floating in space without slowing down... Tap too slowly and the super nova will surly catch up!"
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/supernova.svg"
          altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
          class="project-image"
		  style="background-color: rgb(89, 165, 222)"
        />
        <ProjectCard
          as="div"
          heading="Incrediball"
          subheading="Incrediball is the most incredible endless rolling ball experience. Steer the ball left and right on randomly generated paths to show your friends that you are truly incrediball."
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/beach-ball.svg"
          altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
          class="project-image"
		  style="background-color: wheat;"
        />
        <ProjectCard
          as="div"
          heading="NoiseBean"
          subheading="Personal Discord bot powered by JDA, Spring Boot, and Spring Data JPA. Its can play music from YouTube or act as a soundboard with uploaded files. It also can run private polls, and keep track game play times to collect statistics that players can later view."
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/noisebean.png"
          altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
          class="project-image"
		  style="background-color: #515eff;"
        />
        <ProjectCard
          as="div"
          heading="Checkers Minimax"
          subheading="A full implementation in the Dotnet framework of a playable checkers game against a computer opponent. The artificial intelligence uses the Minimax algorithm to strategize and determine optimal moves based on genetically determined heuristics"
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/checkers.png"
          altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
          class="project-image",
		  style="background-color: brown;"
        />
        <ProjectCard
          as="div"
          heading="Win32ApiHelper"
          subheading="This library was created to assist me in some of my other projects where I required the use of windows specific API functions. The main function of this library is the concept of impersonation and launching processes from a windows service."
          imagePath="/src/assets/icons/win32-library.png"
          altText="Lorem, ipsum dolor sit"
          class="project-image"
		  
        />
      </div>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Skills">
      <SkillLayout title="Languages" skills={languages} />
      <SkillLayout title="Frontend" skills={frontend} />
      <SkillLayout title="Desktop" skills={desktop} />
      <SkillLayout title="Backend" skills={backend} />
      <SkillLayout title="Tools" skills={tools} />
      <SkillLayout title="Others" skills={others} />
    </Section>
  </div>

